race.comment: WINSTON (6) didn't quite measure up to some good 3yo races over the Winter but resumed with a most encouraging win at Mornington over 1500m, settling handy and racing away to score by 1.75 lengths. Should only strip fitter from that and the inside draw should see him land in front. STREET LARK (10) broke through for a smart win at Ballarat when last seen over a mile, settling back off a decent tempo and winning well. She should only improve going to 1800m for the first time. TIVACI CODE (11) is a horse with upside off a dominant Warrnambool maiden win, scoring by 4.5 lengths. Didn't beat much there but has to be respected. CORONA LAD (1) has placed in both runs back and should be competitive again.
